        "execSummary":  "A 20% decline in the blended LLM token expenditure index is a strategically ambiguous data point that enterprise leaders should interpret carefully before drawing conclusions about AI investment trajectories. If the cause is enterprise buyers extracting better pricing through volume negotiations, that is a positive signal of market maturation and improved AI ROI; if it reflects organizational backlash or adoption plateau, it warrants a closer look at whether internal AI programs are delivering measurable value. For customer-support and enterprise AI leaders under pressure to justify AI budgets, this is the moment to get ahead of the ROI measurement challenge ΓÇö organizations that can demonstrate concrete efficiency gains are best positioned regardless of which way token economics move. The shift toward model routing and cheaper-model selection for simpler tasks is likely a structural contributor to the index decline and represents a mature cost-management discipline worth adopting.",
