        "date":  "2026-06-30",
        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "Model routing ΓÇö automatically directing AI requests to the most cost-appropriate model based on task complexity ΓÇö is emerging as the next cost-management abstraction layer for enterprise AI, following the era of unrestricted frontier model usage that drove costs sharply higher. A router evaluates incoming prompts and routes simpler requests to cheaper models, with Coinbase reportedly cutting AI spending in half while increasing total token usage through this approach. The article anticipates a further evolution toward prompt preprocessing layers where AI systems optimize user inputs before routing them to the most appropriate model.",
        "execSummary":  "Model routing represents a practical, immediately deployable cost discipline that enterprise AI leaders can adopt today without waiting for new tooling: the principle that not all prompts require frontier model capability is simple, but the operational savings ΓÇö Coinbase halved spending while growing usage ΓÇö are significant enough to justify dedicated engineering investment. For customer-support operations running high-volume AI workflows, intelligent routing between a frontier model for complex escalations and a lighter model for routine queries could dramatically improve unit economics while maintaining quality at the top of the interaction pyramid. The emerging prompt preprocessing layer, where AI improves the quality of user inputs before routing, is particularly relevant for support contexts where unclear or incomplete customer queries are a persistent efficiency drain. Organizations should treat model routing infrastructure as a strategic asset, not a cost-cutting afterthought, since it will become the default architecture for any enterprise running AI at scale.",
        "vendorLean":  "Neutral",
