        "execSummary":  "The NeurIPS finding that all leading LLMs converge on near-identical outputs for open-ended tasks is a material limitation for enterprises using AI in strategy, ideation, and creative problem-solving contexts where novel thinking is the actual value sought. For AI platform and vendor selection decisions, this introduces a new evaluation criterion: output diversity alongside accuracy and cost, particularly for use cases in marketing, product development, and executive strategy support. The emergence of diversity-optimized models like Flint suggests that model selection will increasingly need to match task type rather than defaulting to a single flagship model across all workflows. The enterprise implication is that teams relying on AI for strategic brainstorming may be unknowingly receiving a narrow slice of the solution space.",
